You agree that you will be responsible for any necessary mobile device software or hardware required to use the Digital Key. Digital Key Handling Policy. You may only use the Digital Key during an eligible stay for which You have a valid reservation for a single guest room at an HWI hotel, resort or other facility owned, managed, or franchised by HWI and for which You have elected (by downloading or accessing) to use a Digital Key (each, a "Participating Property"). Digital Keys licensed to You are specific to Your mobile phone or device and can only be accessed by Your mobile phone or device. You acknowledge and agree that, at this time, only one Digital Key will be able to be issued in connection with any single valid reservation. HWI may change this policy in the future in its sole discretion. Further, Your Digital Key may be used only to unlock the guest room which is registered and assigned to You by HWI. By limiting access, it helps HWI avoid unauthorized usage of Your Digital Key. If at any time while You are using a Digital Key (a) Your mobile phone or device is no longer in Your possession or under Your control for any reason (including, without limitation, because You lost, transferred or assigned it to a third party) or (b) You become aware that Your mobile phone or device has been stolen or otherwise compromised (including, without limitation, if Your mobile phone or device has been hacked or otherwise accessed by an unauthorized third party), You agree to contact the applicable HWI Participating Property as soon as possible and to follow any instructions provided by HWI or a Participating Property (including, without limitation, deleting or consenting to the deletion of any Digital Keys from Your mobile phone or device). HWI and its Participating Properties will not be responsible for any problems or claims that may result from Your failure to notify the applicable Participating Property in the event that Your mobile phone or device is no longer in Your possession, under Your control, or is otherwise compromised.      Mobile Services. In order to use the Digital Key, You agree to ensure that all settings and required network communications necessary to use the Digital Key are enabled and correct, including, without limitation, allowing and enabling push notifications be sent to Your mobile phone or device. You also agree to receive certain communications from HWI in connection with Your Digital Key. You further acknowledge and agree that the Digital Key will only be available for use with certain mobile phones or devices and certain software releases, as designated by HWI in its sole discretion, and therefore, the Digital Key may not be available on all mobile phones or devices or in connection with all operating software. Whenever You make use of Your Digital Key You also agree that (a) Digital Keys can only be used when Bluetooth functionality is enabled on Your mobile phone or device and (b) Digital Keys can only be issued to or deleted from Your mobile phone or device when Your mobile phone or device has network connectivity (e.g., 3G, 4G or wireless Internet connectivity). Please note that Your mobile carrier's normal messaging, data, and other rates and fees will apply to Your utilization of the Digital Key. If Your mobile phone or device does not have network connectivity at any time, You will only be able to use valid Digital Keys already installed on Your mobile phone or device (with Bluetooth connectivity).  You acknowledge that in order to provide the Digital Key, HWI may obtain certain location information about You, for example, use of the Digital Key may result in the collection of geolocation information sent by Your mobile phone or device on which the Digital Key is used, installed, and activated. Digital Key Handling Policy. You may only use the Digital Key during an eligible stay for which You have a valid reservation for a single guest room at an HWI hotel, resort or other facility owned, managed, or franchised by HWI and for which You have elected (by downloading or accessing) to use a Digital Key (each, a "Participating Property"). Digital Keys licensed to You are specific to Your mobile phone or device and can only be accessed by Your mobile phone or device. You acknowledge and agree that, at this time, only one Digital Key will be able to be issued in connection with any single valid reservation. HWI may change this policy in the future in its sole discretion. Further, Your Digital Key may be used only to unlock the guest room which is registered and assigned to You by HWI. By limiting access, it helps HWI avoid unauthorized usage of Your Digital Key. If at any time while You are using a Digital Key (a) Your mobile phone or device is no longer in Your possession or under Your control for any reason (including, without limitation, because You lost, transferred or assigned it to a third party) or (b) You become aware that Your mobile phone or device has been stolen or otherwise compromised (including, without limitation, if Your mobile phone or device has been hacked or otherwise accessed by an unauthorized third party), You agree to contact the applicable HWI Participating Property as soon as possible and to follow any instructions provided by HWI or a Participating Property (including, without limitation, deleting or consenting to the deletion of any Digital Keys from Your mobile phone or device). HWI and its Participating Properties will not be responsible for any problems or claims that may result from Your failure to notify the applicable Participating Property in the event that Your mobile phone or device is no longer in Your possession, under Your control, or is otherwise compromised.      Mobile Services. In order to use the Digital Key, You agree to ensure that all settings and required network communications necessary to use the Digital Key are enabled and correct, including, without limitation, allowing and enabling push notifications be sent to Your mobile phone or device. You also agree to receive certain communications from HWI in connection with Your Digital Key. You further acknowledge and agree that the Digital Key will only be available for use with certain mobile phones or devices and certain software releases, as designated by HWI in its sole discretion, and therefore, the Digital Key may not be available on all mobile phones or devices or in connection with all operating software. Whenever You make use of Your Digital Key You also agree that (a) Digital Keys can only be used when Bluetooth functionality is enabled on Your mobile phone or device and (b) Digital Keys can only be issued to or deleted from Your mobile phone or device when Your mobile phone or device has network connectivity (e.g., 3G, 4G or wireless Internet connectivity). Please note that Your mobile carrier's normal messaging, data, and other rates and fees will apply to Your utilization of the Digital Key. If Your mobile phone or device does not have network connectivity at any time, You will only be able to use valid Digital Keys already installed on Your mobile phone or device (with Bluetooth connectivity).  You acknowledge that in order to provide the Digital Key, HWI may obtain certain location information about You, for example, use of the Digital Key may result in the collection of geolocation information sent by Your mobile phone or device on which the Digital Key is used, installed, and activated. HWI may change this policy in the future in its sole discretion. Further, Your Digital Key may be used only to unlock the guest room which is registered and assigned to You by HWI. By limiting access, it helps HWI avoid unauthorized usage of Your Digital Key. If at any time while You are using a Digital Key (a) Your mobile phone or device is no longer in Your possession or under Your control for any reason (including, without limitation, because You lost, transferred or assigned it to a third party) or (b) You become aware that Your mobile phone or device has been stolen or otherwise compromised (including, without limitation, if Your mobile phone or device has been hacked or otherwise accessed by an unauthorized third party), You agree to contact the applicable HWI Participating Property as soon as possible and to follow any instructions provided by HWI or a Participating Property (including, without limitation, deleting or consenting to the deletion of any Digital Keys from Your mobile phone or device). In order to use the Digital Key, You agree to ensure that all settings and required network communications necessary to use the Digital Key are enabled and correct, including, without limitation, allowing and enabling push notifications be sent to Your mobile phone or device. You also agree to receive certain communications from HWI in connection with Your Digital Key. You further acknowledge and agree that the Digital Key will only be available for use with certain mobile phones or devices and certain software releases, as designated by HWI in its sole discretion, and therefore, the Digital Key may not be available on all mobile phones or devices or in connection with all operating software. Whenever You make use of Your Digital Key You also agree that (a) Digital Keys can only be used when Bluetooth functionality is enabled on Your mobile phone or device and (b) Digital Keys can only be issued to or deleted from Your mobile phone or device when Your mobile phone or device has network connectivity (e.g., 3G, 4G or wireless Internet connectivity). If Your mobile phone or device does not have network connectivity at any time, You will only be able to use valid Digital Keys already installed on Your mobile phone or device (with Bluetooth connectivity).
